What you fail to grasp is just
how replaceable you are!

256
00:20:16,975 --> 00:20:20,337
You're nothing but nice
tits, and a pleasant smile!

257
00:20:20,489 --> 00:20:23,789
You'll be forgotten before
you reach the gate!

258
00:20:27,440 --> 00:20:31,527
This isn't the first time I've been
fucked in a producer's office.

259
00:20:48,699 --> 00:20:49,772
Just you.

260
00:20:49,797 --> 00:20:51,117
Not Dickens.

261
00:20:55,745 --> 00:20:56,964
N.J. Gotlieb.

262
00:20:57,751 --> 00:20:59,144
It's Harry Schrodinger.

263
00:21:00,219 --> 00:21:01,539
Five minutes!

264
00:21:06,091 --> 00:21:08,205
So, he won an Oscar.

265
00:21:08,418 --> 00:21:10,758
He hasn't had a
hit for five years!

266
00:21:11,366 --> 00:21:14,292
But I'm willing to give the rummy
another chance, because

267
00:21:14,533 --> 00:21:15,766
I'm sentimental.

268
00:21:16,266 --> 00:21:18,252
Tell him he's
got 'til 5 o'clock!

269
00:21:18,302 --> 00:21:20,017
Take it, or leave it!

270
00:22:23,041 --> 00:22:24,367
What do you want?

271
00:22:24,938 --> 00:22:26,331
I want to make my report.

272
00:22:26,603 --> 00:22:29,012
- Save it. You're fired.
- I am?

273
00:22:30,806 --> 00:22:33,091
You're fired. I'm fired.

274
00:22:33,139 --> 00:22:34,611
Everybody's fired.

275
00:22:34,879 --> 00:22:36,771
You want to know where
he went last night?

276
00:22:37,435 --> 00:22:39,442
I couldn't care less.

277
00:22:40,533 --> 00:22:43,362
He went to a big house in
the hills above Los Feliz.

278
00:22:45,473 --> 00:22:47,009
You said he went where?

279
00:22:47,593 --> 00:22:49,549
In a house on Glendower Avenue.

280
00:22:51,133 --> 00:22:53,973
- That cow.
- Now, what cow would that be?

281
00:22:54,596 --> 00:22:57,350
- Get that, will ya?
- No, you fired me, remember?

282
00:23:06,552 --> 00:23:07,862
Yeah, it's me.

283
00:23:19,908 --> 00:23:21,336
Am I in your way?

284
00:23:25,902 --> 00:23:27,509
Get them out of here.

285
00:23:28,673 --> 00:23:30,267
All right. Come on.

286
00:23:37,001 --> 00:23:38,015
Hi.

287
00:23:39,861 --> 00:23:41,223
What the hell are
you doing here?

288
00:23:41,247 --> 00:23:43,303
It's go to see you too,
Bradbury. What happened?

289
00:23:43,359 --> 00:23:44,494
Come on, give.

290
00:23:44,766 --> 00:23:46,746
I'm a friend of the
widows. What happened?

291
00:23:47,033 --> 00:23:49,766
Somebody put the big whammy on
Gotlieb and cut him down to size.

292
00:23:49,791 --> 00:23:50,806
Wow!

293
00:23:52,933 --> 00:23:53,745
And...

294
00:23:53,769 --> 00:23:56,527
Ever see two dogs play
tug-of-war with a bone?

295
00:23:57,982 --> 00:24:01,443
Forget the gurney, you can get
him out of here in a lunch pail.

296
00:24:05,500 --> 00:24:07,414
Are you thinking of something?

297
00:24:07,528 --> 00:24:09,613
I'm thinking that, according
to this lady, the last

298
00:24:09,638 --> 00:24:11,914
person to see Gotlieb
before he got small

299
00:24:11,939 --> 00:24:13,614
was your friend the widow.

300
00:24:16,529 --> 00:24:20,596
Okay. Okay. Break it up. This is
a police investigation. Come on.

301
00:24:21,606 --> 00:24:22,899
Lt. Bradbury.

302
00:24:22,953 --> 00:24:24,421
Heard good things about you.

303
00:24:24,445 --> 00:24:25,866
Larson Crockett.

304
00:24:26,806 --> 00:24:29,204
What's being done about
this ghastly business?

305
00:24:29,433 --> 00:24:30,604
We're working on it.

306
00:24:30,985 --> 00:24:32,024
Good!

307
00:24:32,366 --> 00:24:35,472
This is just another example
of how magic has shot its

308
00:24:35,497 --> 00:24:38,463
sinister tentacles into the
motion picture industry.

309
00:24:38,506 --> 00:24:44,581
I give my personal pledge that soon a new
day will dawn on a witch free America.

310
00:24:44,866 --> 00:24:48,467
A more wholesome country,
as we proceed with our

311
00:24:48,492 --> 00:24:51,914
Los Angeles hearings and
prepare our patriotism rally...

312
00:24:51,938 --> 00:24:54,136
I thought the magic
was trouble, but now...

313
00:24:54,503 --> 00:24:56,504
Now that they're trying
to outlaw the stuff...

314
00:24:56,666 --> 00:24:58,055
How come I'm not so happy?

315
00:24:58,080 --> 00:25:00,360
If God doesn't destroy Hollywood

316
00:25:01,200 --> 00:25:04,311
He owes Sodom and
Gomorrah an apology.

317
00:25:06,600 --> 00:25:11,506
As my dear friend Norman Desmond is so fond
of saying, maybe the pictures got small.

318
00:25:11,900 --> 00:25:14,308
But Nicky Gotlieb
never got small.

319
00:25:14,420 --> 00:25:16,286
Well, he did, actually.

320
00:25:16,540 --> 00:25:18,055
But not until the very end.

321
00:25:18,079 --> 00:25:19,863
When he got really small.

322
00:25:20,032 --> 00:25:20,960
Onerous?

323
00:25:20,984 --> 00:25:22,785
You may be the head of a studio.

324
00:25:23,185 --> 00:25:25,219
You may be a big star.

325
00:25:25,251 --> 00:25:28,726
In heaven, we are
all just bit players.

326
00:25:29,300 --> 00:25:32,102
Under contract to the
one who discovered us.

327
00:25:32,480 --> 00:25:33,961
Cecil B. DeMille.

328
00:25:34,366 --> 00:25:35,768
Fatty Arbuckle.

329
00:25:36,432 --> 00:25:37,617
Nicky Gotlieb.

330
00:25:37,675 --> 00:25:39,758
All just walk-ons.

331
00:25:39,915 --> 00:25:41,969
In the part we
were born to play.

332
00:25:42,986 --> 00:25:44,492
God's little extra.

333
00:25:44,792 --> 00:25:47,752
In Nicky's case,
God's very-little extra.

334
00:25:48,340 --> 00:25:50,646
God's littlest extra.

335
00:25:50,966 --> 00:25:54,289
But no less dear to God,
as he was dear to us.

336
00:25:55,913 --> 00:25:58,537
So, farewell, N.J. Gotlieb.

337
00:25:58,933 --> 00:26:01,297
We have reached
the final fade-out.

338
00:26:02,233 --> 00:26:03,719
But, dear friends.

339
00:26:04,366 --> 00:26:06,614
Think of it not so
much as a fade-out,

340
00:26:06,638 --> 00:26:09,252
but as a dissolve
for a fair world.

341
00:26:09,277 --> 00:26:10,466
We have to talk.

342
00:26:12,233 --> 00:26:14,452
Awful nice, you showing
up for his funeral.

343
00:26:14,557 --> 00:26:15,992
I am the widow.

344
00:26:16,600 --> 00:26:18,701
Besides, it'd look
funny if I didn't come.

345
00:26:18,725 --> 00:26:20,294
People might get the wrong idea.

346
00:26:20,319 --> 00:26:21,902
And what idea would that be?

347
00:26:22,025 --> 00:26:23,326
I wanna hire you.

348
00:26:23,919 --> 00:26:26,516
You hire me. You fire me. Now
you wanna hire me again.

349
00:26:26,585 --> 00:26:28,730
I think the police
think I killed Nicky.

350
00:26:28,873 --> 00:26:30,653
- I think you're right.
- I didn't.

351
00:26:30,678 --> 00:26:31,709
Uh-huh.

352
00:26:31,806 --> 00:26:33,048
You believe me, don't you?

353
00:26:33,073 --> 00:26:35,506
Doesn't matter what I believe,
matters what I can prove.

354
00:26:36,579 --> 00:26:37,781
Well, prove it.

355
00:26:37,999 --> 00:26:39,621
Oh! Well, you're
tough, aren't you?

356
00:26:39,645 --> 00:26:40,678
That's me.

357
00:26:40,703 --> 00:26:44,218
Are you tough enough to put your
husband in that parakeet coffin?

358
00:26:45,613 --> 00:26:48,193
Don't strain yourself trying
to figure me out, Lovecraft.

359
00:26:48,366 --> 00:26:50,793
Just find out who killed Nicky,
and get me off the hook.

360
00:26:50,818 --> 00:26:52,493
Can you get the keys to his car?

361
00:26:52,749 --> 00:26:53,624
His car?

362
00:26:53,649 --> 00:26:55,463
The Lincoln he was
driving the other night.

363
00:26:55,646 --> 00:26:57,020
Well, I can get them for you.

364
00:26:58,140 --> 00:27:00,507
I'll start with that, and the
house on Glendower.

365
00:27:00,741 --> 00:27:02,307
Forget about the
house on Glendower.

366
00:27:02,332 --> 00:27:04,035
There's nothing there
you have to know about.

367
00:27:04,060 --> 00:27:07,046
- Well, I'll decide that for myself.
- Stay clear of that place.

368
00:27:07,071 --> 00:27:09,957
You know the cops are only going
to work as hard as they have to.

369
00:27:10,615 --> 00:27:13,451
If the frame fits,
you're gonna wear it.

370
00:27:16,299 --> 00:27:18,379
The keys to the Lincoln
will be at the house.

371
00:28:00,233 --> 00:28:02,469
Somebody slipped me a
Mickey the other night.

372
00:28:03,198 --> 00:28:04,795
What kind of a Mickey?

373
00:28:06,081 --> 00:28:08,408
A raven landed on
the hood of my car.

374
00:28:08,833 --> 00:28:10,961
And the next thing I
know, it's morning.

375
00:28:11,400 --> 00:28:13,931
Ooh, nice touch!

376
00:28:13,955 --> 00:28:16,983
I man, you don't see that kind of
workmanship around these days.

377
00:28:17,008 --> 00:28:18,630
It's usually just frogs.

378
00:28:18,733 --> 00:28:20,874
Not even toads, just frogs.

379
00:28:21,238 --> 00:28:23,054
Oh, but yours...

380
00:28:24,159 --> 00:28:26,355
Anyway, what was the
purpose of this Mickey?

381
00:28:27,533 --> 00:28:29,179
I was following somebody.

382
00:28:29,850 --> 00:28:31,394
And when you woke up,

383
00:28:31,523 --> 00:28:32,550
he was gone.

384
00:28:32,730 --> 00:28:34,008
And now he's dead.

385
00:28:34,032 --> 00:28:35,861
- N.J. Gotlieb.
- The same.

386
00:28:36,131 --> 00:28:38,365
I'm going out to look
at his car, and...

387
00:28:40,166 --> 00:28:41,365
I was...

388
00:28:41,800 --> 00:28:43,964
hoping that maybe
you might go with me.

389
00:28:44,559 --> 00:28:46,118
Are you asking me for help?

390
00:28:46,993 --> 00:28:50,459
Well, I'm asking you to
watch my back for ravens.

391
00:28:50,858 --> 00:28:51,920
Okay?

392
00:28:53,566 --> 00:28:55,477
I have to make a phone call.

393
00:28:59,533 --> 00:29:01,806
So! What are we looking for?

394
00:29:02,632 --> 00:29:03,786
I don't know.

395
00:29:03,979 --> 00:29:05,952
There's sand on
the drivers side.

396
00:29:06,139 --> 00:29:07,692
And none on the passengers.

397
00:29:08,812 --> 00:29:10,654
He went to the beach alone?

398
00:29:10,678 --> 00:29:13,072
Or he went with someone who
didn't come back with him.

399
00:29:14,565 --> 00:29:16,756
Is this what you do
when you detect?

400
00:29:16,879 --> 00:29:18,078
Yeah, basically.

401
00:29:18,478 --> 00:29:21,279
Well, it doesn't seem
very precise to me.

402
00:29:21,451 --> 00:29:23,713
What's buzzin', cousins?

403
00:29:25,592 --> 00:29:27,966
What is this, a field trip?

404
00:29:28,409 --> 00:29:31,969
I had to have somebody watching
my back while I was watching yours.

405
00:29:31,993 --> 00:29:34,752
Besides, Trudy might
be able to help.

406
00:29:35,022 --> 00:29:36,639
God knows I'm willing.

407
00:29:36,962 --> 00:29:38,348
What kinda help?

408
00:29:39,000 --> 00:29:45,001
Events cling to objects, and Trudy is
very good at 'hearing' their memories.

409
00:29:45,104 --> 00:29:46,942
Very, very good.

410
00:29:49,293 --> 00:29:51,314
You want to know what
happened to Gotlieb,

411
00:29:51,339 --> 00:29:53,446
where he and his friend went?

412
00:29:55,433 --> 00:29:56,728
I don't use magic.

413
00:29:56,786 --> 00:29:57,872
Purist!

414
00:29:58,466 --> 00:30:00,347
Who said boo about magic?

415
00:30:00,492 --> 00:30:01,854
You drive the car.

416
00:30:01,991 --> 00:30:03,719
I read the map. That's all.

417
00:30:06,166 --> 00:30:08,448
And what are you, the chaperone?

418
00:30:12,373 --> 00:30:13,706
What about my car?

419
00:30:13,731 --> 00:30:15,806
We have to take this car.

420
00:30:15,938 --> 00:30:17,586
This holds the memories.

421
00:30:18,499 --> 00:30:20,345
It'll be our little secret.

422
00:30:23,552 --> 00:30:25,214
I get the front seat!

423
00:30:35,675 --> 00:30:36,755
Thanks.

424
00:31:06,449 --> 00:31:07,749
Here's where I lost them.

425
00:31:15,012 --> 00:31:17,387
It was raining when
they got back in the car.

426
00:31:18,286 --> 00:31:20,711
Gotlieb, and...

427
00:31:21,593 --> 00:31:22,984
another man.

428
00:31:24,825 --> 00:31:26,714
What am I, the chauffeur?

429
00:31:26,869 --> 00:31:29,962
Never mind. Keep Driving. You're
gonna have the time of your life.

430
00:31:31,313 --> 00:31:32,620
They drove down the hill.

431
00:31:34,270 --> 00:31:35,432
Where do I go?

432
00:31:36,016 --> 00:31:39,124
West on Sunset, all
the way to the beach.

433
00:31:46,386 --> 00:31:48,293
This is where they came.

434
00:32:05,806 --> 00:32:07,208
Now, you can wait here.

435
00:32:07,300 --> 00:32:08,822
You forget, we can help.

436
00:32:08,972 --> 00:32:10,820
I found the house, didn't I?

437
00:32:11,399 --> 00:32:13,574
You want me to tell
you who owns it?

438
00:32:20,298 --> 00:32:21,324
Yes.

439
00:32:21,493 --> 00:32:22,897
I can almost feel it.

440
00:32:23,486 --> 00:32:24,766
It's definitely coming.

441
00:32:25,572 --> 00:32:26,992
Well, when it hits you

442
00:32:27,319 --> 00:32:28,755
would you let me know.

443
00:32:38,480 --> 00:32:40,060
Want me to do that for you?

444
00:32:40,474 --> 00:32:41,540
Do you mind?

445
00:32:48,695 --> 00:32:49,788
All right.

446
00:33:13,239 --> 00:33:14,733
I don't understand.

447
00:33:14,979 --> 00:33:15,985
What?

448
00:33:16,165 --> 00:33:17,372
There's nothing.

449
00:33:19,245 --> 00:33:20,598
Nothing unusual?

450
00:33:20,732 --> 00:33:21,989
Nothing at all.

451
00:33:26,668 --> 00:33:29,632
This place has been
wiped clean, erased, its...

452
00:33:31,085 --> 00:33:32,628
I've never...

453
00:33:33,606 --> 00:33:35,737
It's so empty. What
happened here?

454
00:33:36,866 --> 00:33:39,237
- There was a girl.
- How do you know that?

455
00:33:39,845 --> 00:33:42,165
Doesn't take magic,
there's always a girl.

456
00:33:42,580 --> 00:33:44,748
Trudy, let's take a
look at the bedroom.

457
00:33:46,886 --> 00:33:48,266
Can I ask you something?

458
00:33:48,690 --> 00:33:49,695
No.

459
00:33:49,720 --> 00:33:52,100
What exactly is your
problem with magic?

460
00:33:52,432 --> 00:33:54,198
I don't have a problem.

461
00:33:54,326 --> 00:33:56,063
- I just don't use it.
- Why?

462
00:33:57,261 --> 00:33:58,914
I've got personal reasons.

463
00:33:59,053 --> 00:34:00,243
It's a pity.

464
00:34:00,906 --> 00:34:03,614
Kropotkin says you have
the qualities of a Magus.

465
00:34:04,025 --> 00:34:05,038
To know.

466
00:34:05,278 --> 00:34:06,279
To dare.

467
00:34:06,304 --> 00:34:07,377
To will.

468
00:34:08,239 --> 00:34:09,258
What?

469
00:34:09,639 --> 00:34:13,078
Somebody wiped the prints off the bottle
like they wiped the house of memories.

470
00:34:13,719 --> 00:34:15,812
So you wouldn't know
anyone was here.

471
00:34:15,837 --> 00:34:18,452
The easy thing would have been
to take the bottle and ditch it.

472
00:34:18,477 --> 00:34:19,695
Unless...

473
00:34:19,911 --> 00:34:20,920
Unless?

474
00:34:21,866 --> 00:34:22,979
Unless...

475
00:34:23,146 --> 00:34:25,385
Unless you wanted to make a show

476
00:34:25,719 --> 00:34:28,326
of wiping the prints because...

477
00:34:29,480 --> 00:34:31,738
you want someone know
what you were doing

478
00:34:31,973 --> 00:34:33,549
Why would they do that?

479
00:34:33,846 --> 00:34:35,949
You're the one that
writes screenplays.

480
00:34:36,920 --> 00:34:38,209
You tell me.

481
00:34:40,575 --> 00:34:42,800
Beverly Wilshire
Hotel, good morning.

482
00:34:43,066 --> 00:34:44,513
Room 1209.

483
00:34:44,766 --> 00:34:46,479
I'm sorry, those
calls are being held.

484
00:34:46,504 --> 00:34:48,786
Would you like to leave a
message for Senator Crockett?

485
00:34:49,066 --> 00:34:50,846
Oh, no, that's okay, thanks.

486
00:34:51,399 --> 00:34:52,532
What was that?

487
00:34:54,946 --> 00:34:56,339
Nobody's slept here.

488
00:34:56,713 --> 00:34:57,991
Look at that bed.

489
00:34:59,386 --> 00:35:00,890
There's not a ruffle on it.

490
00:35:01,566 --> 00:35:02,959
It's perfectly smooth.

491
00:35:03,853 --> 00:35:04,961
More show.

492
00:35:08,118 --> 00:35:09,237
Trudy,

493
00:35:09,261 --> 00:35:11,151
it's all right.

494
00:35:11,328 --> 00:35:12,828
No, it's not, it's
not all right!

495
00:35:12,853 --> 00:35:14,614
There's nothing here. Nothing!

496
00:35:15,666 --> 00:35:17,601
Somebody sucked the
life out of this place.

497
00:35:17,625 --> 00:35:19,326
It's so empty it
makes my head hurt.

498
00:35:19,619 --> 00:35:21,799
It's all right, kid.
You did your best.

499
00:35:22,471 --> 00:35:23,834
You don't understand.

500
00:35:24,074 --> 00:35:26,462
This place is dead,
as dead as the moon.

501
00:35:26,560 --> 00:35:28,201
That's not right at all.

502
00:35:39,155 --> 00:35:41,303
Two rules you learn
in this business.

503
00:35:41,501 --> 00:35:42,808
Get paid up front

504
00:35:42,953 --> 00:35:44,975
and don't work with partners.

505
00:35:51,928 --> 00:35:54,221
The bathroom wasn't
empty after all.

506
00:35:55,672 --> 00:35:59,547
Someone had left a stem of
a martini glass from the bar.

507
00:36:00,765 --> 00:36:02,072
More show?

508
00:36:04,200 --> 00:36:06,809
It took us three hours to
get home from Malibu.

509
00:36:07,025 --> 00:36:10,008
Then Trudy made us stop
to listen to a building.

510
00:36:33,132 --> 00:36:34,339
Jesus!

511
00:36:36,939 --> 00:36:39,025
You see that? You
see what he done?

512
00:36:39,050 --> 00:36:40,092
Frisk him.

513
00:36:53,012 --> 00:36:54,039
Move.

514
00:36:54,306 --> 00:36:55,322
Where?

515
00:36:55,585 --> 00:36:57,536
You're interested in
