01:11:37,924 --> 01:11:39,504
And she does what?

1025
01:11:39,832 --> 01:11:40,857
Well,

1026
01:11:41,278 --> 01:11:43,212
when they wanted
to set someone up,

1027
01:11:43,501 --> 01:11:45,607
they let the sex
get a little rough.

1028
01:11:46,333 --> 01:11:50,181
Then Marie hits her head
or slips in the bathtub,

1029
01:11:51,178 --> 01:11:52,208
and drowns.

1030
01:11:52,813 --> 01:11:53,841
Macha shows up,

1031
01:11:54,633 --> 01:11:57,541
says everything can be
taken care of for a price.

1032
01:11:58,092 --> 01:11:59,578
The patsy pays, leaves.

1033
01:12:00,757 --> 01:12:03,130
Marie's free to
play another day.

1034
01:12:06,166 --> 01:12:08,506
So that's what happened
at the beach house.

1035
01:12:09,253 --> 01:12:11,026
They're shaking
down the senator,

1036
01:12:11,685 --> 01:12:13,098
Something goes wrong.

1037
01:12:24,858 --> 01:12:26,399
Presto change-o.

1038
01:12:27,512 --> 01:12:29,281
What's wrong with
having what you want?

1039
01:12:33,126 --> 01:12:34,619
I just wanted to be happy.

1040
01:12:35,418 --> 01:12:36,932
They got pills for that now.

1041
01:12:38,638 --> 01:12:39,802
Phew! Water!

1042
01:12:40,992 --> 01:12:42,182
Water everywhere.

1043
01:12:44,259 --> 01:12:45,826
You don't know everything.

1044
01:12:47,059 --> 01:12:48,865
You don't have the
magic in your blood.

1045
01:12:49,466 --> 01:12:51,899
You don't have it on your
skin every day of your life.

1046
01:12:53,279 --> 01:12:54,299
No,

1047
01:12:54,966 --> 01:12:57,966
but I used to once, a
long time ago, just once.

1048
01:13:00,633 --> 01:13:01,658
There were two men,

1049
01:13:02,333 --> 01:13:05,153
they're going out on a boat and
I needed to hear what they said.

1050
01:13:06,666 --> 01:13:08,750
So I hid an empty
bottle on board,

1051
01:13:10,033 --> 01:13:11,638
and when they came back,

1052
01:13:12,798 --> 01:13:14,028
I took the bottle,

1053
01:13:15,900 --> 01:13:17,880
and I poured the
conversation out,

1054
01:13:19,200 --> 01:13:20,650
and I had what I needed.

1055
01:13:21,633 --> 01:13:24,414
But they weren't alone on
the boat, there was a girl.

1056
01:13:25,086 --> 01:13:26,786
So when the cops came after 'em,

1057
01:13:27,245 --> 01:13:28,978
they figured the
girl had ratted.

1058
01:13:29,405 --> 01:13:30,558
Cops got 'em both,

1059
01:13:30,852 --> 01:13:32,318
but before they did,

1060
01:13:32,552 --> 01:13:33,585
one of 'em

1061
01:13:34,333 --> 01:13:35,376
had time

1062
01:13:36,015 --> 01:13:37,942
to take her back
out on that boat

1063
01:13:39,379 --> 01:13:40,676
strangle her,

1064
01:13:42,299 --> 01:13:44,317
and throw her body in the bay.

1065
01:13:48,519 --> 01:13:49,565
Am now,

1066
01:13:52,873 --> 01:13:54,225
the man and the bottle

1067
01:13:56,179 --> 01:13:57,461
has come back.

1068
01:14:09,259 --> 01:14:10,882
Busy, busy, busy.

1069
01:14:11,632 --> 01:14:13,566
Rush, rush, rush!

1070
01:14:15,045 --> 01:14:16,404
How'd you get up here?

1071
01:14:17,665 --> 01:14:20,359
You forget, somebody
showed me the back way.

1072
01:14:22,139 --> 01:14:23,452
Where's Mocha?

1073
01:14:26,118 --> 01:14:27,591
Was it your idea

1074
01:14:27,757 --> 01:14:30,008
or Mocha's, to set up Crockett
in the badger game?

1075
01:14:30,033 --> 01:14:31,111
I know it wasn't Gotlieb,

1076
01:14:31,136 --> 01:14:33,257
all he wanted to do was
show him a good time.

1077
01:14:33,596 --> 01:14:35,428
I don't know what
you're talking about.

1078
01:14:35,822 --> 01:14:37,288
I'm not interested in you.

1079
01:14:38,012 --> 01:14:39,147
Finn Mocha!

1080
01:14:39,710 --> 01:14:41,952
Oh, he's something
else again, isn't he?

1081
01:14:42,240 --> 01:14:45,139
I'm done with Macha, that
partnership is dissolved.

1082
01:14:45,164 --> 01:14:47,824
I'm taking a long,
long, vacation.

1083
01:14:48,939 --> 01:14:49,972
Where is he?

1084
01:14:56,127 --> 01:14:57,220
He's leaving.

1085
01:14:58,272 --> 01:14:59,640
I'm a lucky man.

1086
01:14:59,878 --> 01:15:03,156
I don't suppose you need any help
with your luggage, do you, Vivian?

1087
01:15:03,912 --> 01:15:04,916
Guess not.

1088
01:15:14,499 --> 01:15:16,365
Watch the noise, fellas.

1089
01:15:20,526 --> 01:15:22,213
You know what they
say about zombies?

1090
01:15:22,238 --> 01:15:23,061
What?

1091
01:15:23,086 --> 01:15:24,300
Strong as hell,

1092
01:15:24,826 --> 01:15:27,524
but very bad lateral movement.

1093
01:16:05,746 --> 01:16:06,746
Mint?

1094
01:16:21,413 --> 01:16:24,020
Let's try it one more
time. Where's Mocha?

1095
01:16:35,297 --> 01:16:36,804
Get your flags!

1096
01:16:57,440 --> 01:16:59,606
Evening, Lovecraft,
glad you could make it.

1097
01:17:00,279 --> 01:17:01,390
How much is in there?

1098
01:17:01,878 --> 01:17:05,396
Oh, not so much in the
grand scheme of things.

1099
01:17:05,839 --> 01:17:07,710
Expediting pays pretty good.

1100
01:17:07,970 --> 01:17:09,430
So does discretion.

1101
01:17:09,912 --> 01:17:13,259
You had Gotlieb killed. You thought he
was the one working the badger game.

1102
01:17:13,766 --> 01:17:15,819
I'm afraid I went off
a little half-cocked.

1103
01:17:15,980 --> 01:17:17,113
And the girl.

1104
01:17:17,203 --> 01:17:18,319
Loose ends, Phil.

1105
01:17:18,343 --> 01:17:20,429
You know how I am
about loose ends.

1106
01:17:22,166 --> 01:17:24,372
And, whose idea was it to

1107
01:17:24,485 --> 01:17:25,726
set up Kropotkin?

1108
01:17:25,938 --> 01:17:26,939
Mine.

1109
01:17:27,336 --> 01:17:30,313
The senator wanted to use
Kim, but I convinced him that

1110
01:17:30,337 --> 01:17:33,513
the frame would be a
better fit using the witch.

1111
01:17:33,731 --> 01:17:35,899
So,

1112
01:17:35,900 --> 01:17:37,493
this guy's

1113
01:17:38,033 --> 01:17:39,466
gonna blackmail you

1114
01:17:40,300 --> 01:17:42,720
and now you're acting
like long lost brothers.

1115
01:17:43,566 --> 01:17:46,425
Politics makes strange
bedfellows, I guess.

1116
01:17:46,503 --> 01:17:48,149
But he's a practitioner!

1117
01:17:50,572 --> 01:17:51,602
So?

1118
01:17:52,679 --> 01:17:54,092
It was all a show.

1119
01:17:59,018 --> 01:18:01,317
The hearings, the
press coverage.

1120
01:18:02,100 --> 01:18:05,886
Attacking magic. You could care
less about protecting the people.

1121
01:18:07,900 --> 01:18:12,166
Spend some time in congress, Phil.
You get up-to-here with the people.

1122
01:18:13,206 --> 01:18:15,579
Listening to their
petty complaints,

1123
01:18:15,604 --> 01:18:18,693
their demands, their
constant inane whining

1124
01:18:18,718 --> 01:18:22,265
about one thing after the next thing,
after the next thing, after the next thing!

1125
01:18:22,388 --> 01:18:25,366
Just because they vote for you,
they think you owe them something!

1126
01:18:25,632 --> 01:18:27,873
But why go after magic?

1127
01:18:29,519 --> 01:18:31,215
Who am I supposed to go after?

1128
01:18:31,665 --> 01:18:32,945
Big business?

1129
01:18:33,325 --> 01:18:36,218
You need something a little
different, a little outside.

1130
01:18:37,178 --> 01:18:40,061
Let me tell you something
about the people, Phil.

1131
01:18:40,933 --> 01:18:43,001
You lock any ten
of 'em in a room,

1132
01:18:43,566 --> 01:18:45,072
they may not elect a leader,

1133
01:18:45,473 --> 01:18:48,433
but I guarantee they'll
pick someone to hate.

1134
01:18:53,591 --> 01:18:56,464
Burn the witch,
burn the witch...

1135
01:18:56,728 --> 01:18:58,591
Back up! Back up!

1136
01:19:02,396 --> 01:19:03,996
Stay back!

1137
01:19:04,671 --> 01:19:06,051
Come on! Back off!

1138
01:19:06,828 --> 01:19:07,994
Stay back!

1139
01:19:13,019 --> 01:19:15,019
I'm not gonna let you burn her.

1140
01:19:15,158 --> 01:19:18,866
The witch will burn, and there's
nothing you can do about it.

1141
01:19:19,364 --> 01:19:21,344
You'd be surprised
what I can do.

1142
01:19:21,437 --> 01:19:22,484
Really?

1143
01:19:23,412 --> 01:19:24,570
Gentleman.

1144
01:19:26,165 --> 01:19:27,886
Did you hear everything?

1145
01:19:28,097 --> 01:19:29,165
Yes, sir.

1146
01:19:30,060 --> 01:19:32,185
What was the gist of
our conversation?

1147
01:19:32,772 --> 01:19:35,985
They brought money in that satchel,
they thought they could pay you off.

1148
01:19:38,099 --> 01:19:39,281
Well then,

1149
01:19:40,133 --> 01:19:41,369
you'd better arrest them.

1150
01:19:41,394 --> 01:19:43,207
What are you trying
to pull, Crockett?

1151
01:19:44,266 --> 01:19:45,879
I'd better take
that for evidence.

1152
01:19:46,766 --> 01:19:49,312
No one double
crosses Finn Macha!

1153
01:19:49,395 --> 01:19:51,216
I'm the one that sees inside.

1154
01:19:51,466 --> 01:19:53,905
If you don't believe
me, ask Lovecraft.

1155
01:19:54,592 --> 01:19:57,992
I see what's inside,
and I bring it out!

1156
01:19:58,276 --> 01:20:00,692
What you are is an
insignificant little Mick.

1157
01:20:02,945 --> 01:20:05,933
The crack of Solomon
on your heart.

1158
01:20:13,959 --> 01:20:15,099
Bring them both.

1159
01:20:15,364 --> 01:20:16,986
I don't want them
to miss the show.

1160
01:20:18,772 --> 01:20:20,492
What did you just do?

1161
01:21:45,839 --> 01:21:47,741
Someone just remarked...

1162
01:21:47,765 --> 01:21:51,733
This could make a great movie.
Wil, work on something, will ya?

1163
01:21:51,757 --> 01:21:55,512
Well, I think we have
something just as special.

1164
01:21:55,536 --> 01:22:00,869
Ladies and gentlemen, the next president
of the United States, Larson Crockett!

1165
01:22:12,477 --> 01:22:13,824
America,

1166
01:22:14,644 --> 01:22:16,377
is going to be...

1167
01:22:16,802 --> 01:22:17,956
all right!

1168
01:22:21,058 --> 01:22:24,584
And it's going to be all right
because of people like you!

1169
01:22:26,653 --> 01:22:27,695
God...

1170
01:22:29,988 --> 01:22:32,230
God, I love this country.

1171
01:22:39,286 --> 01:22:41,341
The fire we light tonight

1172
01:22:42,000 --> 01:22:43,886
will burn across America.

1173
01:22:44,179 --> 01:22:45,992
It will set fires

1174
01:22:46,533 --> 01:22:48,019
in every city

1175
01:22:49,232 --> 01:22:50,645
and every town.

1176
01:22:52,071 --> 01:22:53,625
Can I count on you?

1177
01:22:59,159 --> 01:23:00,699
Can I depend on you?

1178
01:23:02,715 --> 01:23:04,668
Of course I can!

1179
01:23:33,303 --> 01:23:35,104
We know the difference

1180
01:23:37,536 --> 01:23:41,429
- Between right and wrong.
- No one double-crosses Finn Macha.

1181
01:23:41,654 --> 01:23:42,767
And we know

1182
01:23:44,264 --> 01:23:45,324
our cause...

1183
01:23:53,588 --> 01:23:55,388
The cameras, the cameras!

1184
01:23:55,413 --> 01:23:57,684
The cameras? Off, now!

1185
01:24:38,939 --> 01:24:41,400
That feels good!

1186
01:24:41,719 --> 01:24:44,234
Nothing like a little fresh air!

1187
01:24:45,899 --> 01:24:47,745
Looks like we're
having a little party!

1188
01:24:48,220 --> 01:24:50,272
Well, guess who just showed up?

1189
01:24:51,573 --> 01:24:52,602
Hey!

1190
01:24:53,260 --> 01:24:54,955
What the fuck you lookin' at?

1191
01:24:56,865 --> 01:24:57,929
Come on!

1192
01:24:58,246 --> 01:24:59,836
Time to burn the witch.

1193
01:25:00,396 --> 01:25:02,534
Come on, we're gonna burn her,

1194
01:25:02,559 --> 01:25:05,715
then we're gonna burn another one, and
another one, and another one after that.

1195
01:25:05,744 --> 01:25:08,137
We're gonna stack
'em up like firewood!

1196
01:25:08,597 --> 01:25:10,282
Come on, what's wrong
with you people?

1197
01:25:10,421 --> 01:25:12,742
You're pretty loud when
you want something!

1198
01:25:14,964 --> 01:25:17,111
Oh, Senator Crockett,

1199
01:25:17,209 --> 01:25:19,218
I-I deserve better.

1200
01:25:19,242 --> 01:25:22,629
Oh, Senator Crockett,
I deserve a better life!

1201
01:25:22,702 --> 01:25:27,948
Oh, Senator Crockett, I deserve TV
dinners, and T-birds, and lawns to cut!

1202
01:25:27,973 --> 01:25:29,304
And peace of mind.

1203
01:25:29,328 --> 01:25:32,299
Well, I got news for all of
you, you're not gonna get it!

1204
01:25:32,324 --> 01:25:34,178
I'll tell you what
you're gonna get,

1205
01:25:34,203 --> 01:25:39,043
porno video, and double-digit
inflation, and a designated hitter.

1206
01:25:39,089 --> 01:25:42,175
And wars in countries
you never even heard of!

1207
01:25:42,653 --> 01:25:45,826
Now that's what I call
a world without magic!

1208
01:25:46,030 --> 01:25:47,099
Hey!

1209
01:25:47,380 --> 01:25:48,880
Where you all going?!

1210
01:25:49,393 --> 01:25:51,259
The party just started.

1211
01:25:51,613 --> 01:25:53,886
I thought you wanted
me to help you out!

1212
01:25:54,665 --> 01:25:56,945
I thought you liked me!

1213
01:25:59,363 --> 01:26:00,750
Ah, fuck it!

1214
01:26:01,128 --> 01:26:03,121
I'll do it myself.

1215
01:26:05,388 --> 01:26:06,854
Go on, arrest him!

1216
01:26:06,879 --> 01:26:08,354
Arrest both of them.

1217
01:26:08,379 --> 01:26:10,635
Your names? I want
both your names!

1218
01:26:12,417 --> 01:26:13,830
Let go, you!

1219
01:26:14,969 --> 01:26:16,797
I have friends in high places!

1220
01:26:18,415 --> 01:26:19,589
Come on.

1221
01:26:27,139 --> 01:26:28,359
Where's Macha?

1222
01:26:28,458 --> 01:26:30,906
I don't know. He took off when
Crockett came out of his shell.

1223
01:26:30,931 --> 01:26:33,271
I gotta find him. We've got
some unfinished business.

1224
01:26:43,545 --> 01:26:46,233
It seems he feels
the same way too.

1225
01:27:22,566 --> 01:27:23,701
You stay here.

1226
01:27:23,725 --> 01:27:25,239
You shouldn't do this alone.

1227
01:27:25,851 --> 01:27:27,066
Yes, I should.

1228
01:27:27,882 --> 01:27:31,118
Some people use magic
for gain or revenge,

1229
01:27:31,142 --> 01:27:34,143
But Macha... Macha
uses it out of malice.

1230
01:27:34,168 --> 01:27:37,948
It's not just his eye
that's sour, it's his soul.

1231
01:27:38,938 --> 01:27:41,735
Then I guess you better
keep the motor running.

1232
01:28:04,075 --> 01:28:07,608
Lovely of you to come, Phillip,
and at such short notice.

1233
01:28:30,006 --> 01:28:32,600
So how'd things work out
with Senator Crockett?

1234
01:28:33,966 --> 01:28:35,640
They're trying to
put him together.

1235
01:28:36,086 --> 01:28:38,880
No one double-crosses
Finn Macha.

1236
01:28:40,546 --> 01:28:42,562
Too bad you left before the end.

1237
01:28:43,566 --> 01:28:45,422
But that wasn't
the end, Phillip.

1238
01:28:46,247 --> 01:28:48,427
This is it, right here.

1239
01:28:49,700 --> 01:28:50,780
Where is she?

1240
01:28:51,960 --> 01:28:53,153
Where's Kim?

1241
01:28:56,432 --> 01:28:58,931
I haven't forgotten that
business with the bottle.

1242
01:28:59,817 --> 01:29:00,992
I figure,

1243
01:29:01,016 --> 01:29:02,950
once a man uses magic,

1244
01:29:03,566 --> 01:29:04,877
he may use it again.

1245
01:29:05,412 --> 01:29:07,812
And I want that man on my team.

1246
01:29:09,242 --> 01:29:10,752
I don't use magic.

1247
01:29:11,326 --> 01:29:12,605
We'll see.

1248
01:29:13,148 --> 01:29:14,509
I ask you a question.

1249
01:29:14,533 --> 01:29:16,361
Well, where do you
think she might be?

1250
01:29:18,246 --> 01:29:20,360
I'm a fan of old movies.

1251
01:29:20,926 --> 01:29:23,887
I like to watch them
over, and over.

1252
01:29:24,646 --> 01:29:26,677
And there's one I'd
like to show you.

1253
01:29:28,553 --> 01:29:30,601
Except, it's not that old.

1254
01:29:31,971 --> 01:29:33,641
Just a couple of days.

1255
01:29:34,932 --> 01:29:36,271
Come along, Phillip.

1256
01:29:37,145 --> 01:29:38,867
Here's my screening room.

1257
01:29:45,840 --> 01:29:47,468
And this is my movie.

1258
01:29:49,959 --> 01:29:53,149
- Call me Mr. President again.
- Mr. President.

1259
01:29:59,846 --> 01:30:01,060
Take a seat.

1260
01:30:06,566 --> 01:30:10,203
A wonderful thing about old
movies is you get to recast them.

1261
01:30:10,519 --> 01:30:13,471
Take this one for instance,
it wasn't cast right.

1262
01:30:21,699 --> 01:30:23,335
That's much better.

1263
01:30:27,933 --> 01:30:29,675
I've also done a little rewrite.

1264
01:30:29,699 --> 01:30:31,452
In the original,
the girl didn't die,

1265
01:30:31,477 --> 01:30:34,139
but considering the
new cast, she will.

1266
01:30:36,566 --> 01:30:38,255
Well, aren't you
going to do anything?

1267
01:30:40,200 --> 01:30:41,724
Think of the little lady.

1268
01:30:49,138 --> 01:30:50,308
Let her go.

1269
01:30:50,485 --> 01:30:51,844
Well, you could make me.

1270
01:30:52,179 --> 01:30:54,787
You could whip up some
of the Mojo Hoodoo.

1271
01:30:54,899 --> 01:30:57,397
Conjure up a lightning
bolt and strike me down.

1272
01:30:57,421 --> 01:30:58,982
You want some incentive?

1273
01:31:01,672 --> 01:31:02,799
No!

1274
01:31:04,172 --> 01:31:05,782
You have the power!

1275
01:31:06,037 --> 01:31:08,521
You know the words!
You know the spells!

1276
01:31:08,685 --> 01:31:11,540
You let one girl die
because you used magic.

1277
01:31:11,564 --> 01:31:14,079
Are you going to let another
one die because you won't!

1278
01:31:14,445 --> 01:31:16,527
Work for me, Phil.

1279
01:31:22,100 --> 01:31:25,200
Darling, you're about
to die of principles.

1280
01:31:28,812 --> 01:31:30,865
I don't use magic.

1281
01:31:30,995 --> 01:31:32,738
Well, the pity is,

1282
01:31:33,035 --> 01:31:34,244
I do.

1283
01:31:36,933 --> 01:31:38,118
Help me.

1284
01:32:14,433 --> 01:32:17,141
Water, water, everywhere.

1285
01:32:43,302 --> 01:32:46,109
I'm sorry, Phil, I
couldn't let you do it.

1286
01:32:47,246 --> 01:32:48,969
I flipped the bird.

1287
01:32:57,172 --> 01:32:58,719
- Here you go.
- Thank you.

1288
01:33:00,252 --> 01:33:02,205
You sure this is what
you want to do?

1289
01:33:02,912 --> 01:33:04,118
Pretty sure.

1290
01:33:04,712 --> 01:33:07,312
Well, the public's gonna wonder
what happened to Kim Hudson.

1291
01:33:07,438 --> 01:33:09,572
Well, if they want
to wonder, let 'em.

1292
01:33:14,820 --> 01:33:16,623
Well, thanks.

1293
01:33:17,142 --> 01:33:18,286
Good luck.

1294
01:33:19,959 --> 01:33:20,972
Bye.

1295
01:33:24,039 --> 01:33:25,166
Wait a second.

1296
01:33:28,225 --> 01:33:29,655
There's something we forgot.

1297
01:33:29,795 --> 01:33:30,815
What?

1298
01:33:55,393 --> 01:33:56,490
Wow!

1299
01:33:57,020 --> 01:33:59,539
A girl could last the
winter on a kiss like that.

1300
01:34:08,547 --> 01:34:09,967
Don't forget to write.

1301
01:34:11,101 --> 01:34:12,541
Oh, I won't.

1302
01:34:24,806 --> 01:34:26,567
Kim Hudson disappeared.

1303
01:34:27,383 --> 01:34:29,650
But since she never
really existed,

1304
01:34:29,959 --> 01:34:31,823
I figured the score was even.

1305
01:34:32,929 --> 01:34:34,570
It didn't matter anyway,

1306
01:34:34,594 --> 01:34:38,040
pretty soon another girl would
be stepping off the Highland bus,

1307
01:34:38,328 --> 01:34:41,934
wishing herself into a
D-cup, and her big break.

1308
01:34:42,419 --> 01:34:43,760
Crockett, too.

1309
01:34:43,973 --> 01:34:45,600
He's the kind of guy

1310
01:34:45,624 --> 01:34:47,613
who says he hates magic

1311
01:34:47,637 --> 01:34:51,364
and then goes home and
levitates chicks in the basement.

1312
01:34:51,844 --> 01:34:55,857
Last I heard, he was sharing a
cell with himself in San Quentin.

1313
01:34:57,599 --> 01:34:59,030
And so it goes.

1314
01:34:59,991 --> 01:35:03,940
There was usually a one-to-one ratio
between dreams and disappointments,

1315
01:35:03,965 --> 01:35:06,124
and no amount of magic
could change that.

1316
01:35:06,289 --> 01:35:09,378
It's always gonna be there if
someone wants to believe in it.

1317
01:35:10,192 --> 01:35:11,349
Let's face it,

1318
01:35:11,846 --> 01:35:13,811
everybody's gotta
believe in something.

